			<ns0:name>k...@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/112268664018567406585/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">We allow "mov %rsp, %rbp" as performance optimization. This will be forbidden.

Also: we can not use pushl to save stack: pushl is unavailable in x86-64 mode.

We can du all stack manipulations manually without using push/pop instructions, but it looks like overkill.

This is interesting idea, but it'll only make sense if/when PNaCl will reach "usable and widespread" stage. And this may be long time in coming.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2010-12-10T21:27:29.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2010-12-10T21:27:29.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:updates /><ns0:title>Comment 6 by k...@chromium.org</ns0:title><ns0:link href="http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=1235#c6" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><ns0:link href="https://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/1235/comments/full/6" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /></ns0:entry>